name: 1-Benzyl-1H-benzotriazole-4-carboxylic acid

- Carboxylic acid group: +40°C (due to its capability of strong hydrogen bonding, which increases intermolecular forces.)
- Benzyl group: +30°C (due to increase in the molecular weight and hydrophobic interactions.)
-Additional aromatic ring (as part of the benzotriazole ring system): included in the +130°C adjustment.
These contributions are additive because each functional group contributes to the overall molecular stability and the intermolecular forces present in the solid state.
